.TH git-sqlite-clean 1 "January 2026" "git-sqlite-filter" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
git-sqlite-clean \- Git clean filter for SQLite databases
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B git-sqlite-clean
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] \fIFILE\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B git-sqlite-clean
is an intelligent Git filter that converts binary SQLite databases into deterministic SQL dumps.
It performs noise reduction by sorting rows by Primary Key and rounding floats to prevent phantom diffs.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-float\-precision \fIN\fR
Round floating point numbers to \fIN\fR decimal places.
.TP
.B \-\-data\-only
Output only INSERT statements, skipping schema.
.TP
.B \-\-schema\-only
Output only schema definitions, skipping data.
.TP
.B \-\-debug
Output diagnostic information to stderr.
.SH SEE ALSO
git-sqlite-smudge(1)
